{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1cd4e3f7-a97d-413d-b61b-477d7cf38cc1","content":"The switch is straightforward. In your project file, **remove** (or set to `false`) the VSTest property:\n\n```xml\n<!-- Remove this line -->\n<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>\n```\n\nThat's it. With **MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0**, `Microsoft.Testing.Platform` is the **default** runner. The `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>` property was explicitly opting you *out* of it. By removing it, you opt back in.\n\n### Things to verify after the change\n\n1. **`dotnet test`** — should work as before.\n2. **Command-line differences** — the new platform uses `--` to pass runner options (e.g., `dotnet test -- --filter \"Name=Foo\"`).\n3. **`.runsettings`** — still supported, but some adapter-specific nodes may behave differently.\n4. **CI pipelines** — if you rely on TRX output, add `--results-directory` and ensure `--logger trx` is passed.\n5. **Third-party extensions** (e.g., coverlet, Playwright) — confirm they support `Microsoft.Testing.Platform`; some still require VSTest adapters.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d734169e-1cb7-4fec-8110-7421eb888699","outputTokens":290,"requestId":"E3D0:1A0B9E:161DE43:18BB33E:6A052008"},"id":"794d1b2f-86e9-4511-aea6-17410d99b9b2","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:06:25.120Z","parentId":"4ea11ebd-2895-4126-bfb7-86b126903897"}
